<TITLE> Barca claim place in semis after 1-0 win over Schalke </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BARCELONA, April 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Barcelona claimed their place in the semi-finals of the Champions League after a goal from midfielder Yaya Toure gave them a nervy 1-0 win over Schalke 04 at the Nou Camp on Wednesday. Barca, 1-0 up after the first leg in Gelsenkirchen, were put under severe pressure in the opening half hour, but the Schalke storm blew itself out just before halftime and the Catalans were gifted a goal after a series of mishaps in the German defence. Toure scuffed the ball in from close range in the 43rd minute after a Bojan Krkic cross from the right had ballooned off the foot of a defender and was then headed off the line. The goal steadied the Catalans and although there were sporadic threats from Schalke in the second half they shut the Germans out to gain a victory that will help placate their discontented fans who have been protesting about their poor form in the leagu
